[I] Archive manager

[T] Ark is a graphical file compression/decompression utility with support for
[T] multiple formats, including tar, gzip, bzip2, rar and zip, as well as
[T] CD-ROM images. Ark can be used to browse, extract, create, and modify
[T] archives.

[U] https://apps.kde.org/ark/

[A] The KDE-Team
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/office extra/desktop/kde
[F] CROSS OBJDIR

[L] GPL
[V] 25.12.3

[CV-GROUP] kde-gear
